---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout title="Division 2 Expertise Cost Tracker | DivGaming" canonical="/division-2/tools/expertise-cost-tracker/">
  <section class="shell hero compact-hero">
    <div class="page-hero">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Expertise Planning</p>
        <h1>Plan upgrade priorities before spending materials</h1>
        <p class="lead">Use this page as a clean launch point for Expertise planning, item lookup, and upgrade decisions. Full material formulas should only be published once they are verified against the current season.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button primary" href={`${base}/division-2/tools/named-items-database/`}>Research named items</a>
          <a class="button ghost" href={`${base}/division-2/tools/exotic-source-tracker/`}>Check exotics</a>
          <a class="button ghost" href={`${base}/division-2/builds/`}>Open builds</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="hero-panel">
        <span>Upgrade Path</span>
        <strong>Expertise</strong>
        <small>Planning hub</small>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="shell section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Upgrade discipline</p>
      <h2>Spend materials on items you actually use</h2>
      <p>Start with the build you play, confirm the item, then decide whether the upgrade is worth the material cost.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-grid">
      <a class="feature-card primary-card" href={`${base}/division-2/builds/`}>
        <span>Step 1</span>
        <strong>Pick the build</strong>
        <p>Do not upgrade random inventory. Start from a build and upgrade the pieces that stay equipped.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="feature-card" href={`${base}/division-2/tools/named-items-database/`}>
        <span>Step 2</span>
        <strong>Confirm the item</strong>
        <p>Use the item databases to verify the named item, slot, role, and talent before investing.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="feature-card" href={`${base}/division-2/tools/vendor-reset/`}>
        <span>Step 3</span>
        <strong>Watch vendors</strong>
        <p>Vendor stock can shortcut farming for items and rolls you plan to upgrade.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
